Directory structure:

└── dev-khanna-dataqualityagent/
    ├── README
    ├── config.py
    ├── main.py
    ├── orchestrator.py
    ├── state.py
    ├── knowledge_base/
    │   └── dq_checks.md
    ├── tools/
    │   ├── __init__.py
    │   ├── database_tools.py
    │   ├── report_tools.py
    │   ├── rule_tools.py
    │   └── sql_tools.py
    └── utils/
        ├── database.py
        └── helpers.py

Control Flow:

main.py
└─ for each table:
   └─ orchestrator.py (LangGraph agent loop, via create_agent)
      └─ repeatedly calls ONE of six tools, reads result, decides next:
         1. extract_database_metadata   (tools/database_tools.py)
         2. create_rule_plan            (tools/rule_tools.py)
         3. generate_sql                (tools/sql_tools.py)
         4. validate_sql                (tools/sql_tools.py)
         5. execute_sql                 (tools/sql_tools.py)
         6. write_report                (tools/report_tools.py)
      └─ ends when the orchestrator replies with plain text
         instead of calling another tool
└─ main.py re-reads the report from disk before starting the next table
